I'll walk you through setting up this Spring Boot + Thymeleaf project in IntelliJ IDEA from scratch, step by step.
Step 1: Create a New Spring Boot Project
Open IntelliJ IDEA
Click File → New → Project
In the left panel, select Spring Initializr
Fill in the details:
Name: thymeleafsample
Group: com.example
Artifact: thymeleafsample
Language: Java
Type: Maven
Java version: 17
Packaging: Jar
Click Next
Step 2: Add Dependencies
On the dependencies screen, search for and select:
✅ Spring Web (under Web)
✅ Thymeleaf (under Template Engines)
✅ Spring Security (under Security)
✅ Spring Data JPA (under SQL)
✅ MySQL Driver (under SQL)
✅ Lombok (under Developer Tools)
Click Create.
